column5: Took a drive to Dave's (fish finder charters) in Trenton to have a look at the ice and it's good. His huts are going out and he will be open tomorrow for business. He said ice has been bad this year but looks good by his place now. Fishing should be good with all the mild weather we have had. With this cold snap it's making good ice. Will be going out next weekend and see if I can hook a few eyes and jumbo perch.
Nice to finally see some ice down there.  Good for the businesses and the
seems everything is starting to firm up
